article.headline: (22) PITTSBURGH 90, ST FRANCIS PA 69
article.story:
PITTSBURGH (Ticker) -- Pittsburgh at home against in-state 
rival St. Francis was a perfect situation for the 22nd-ranked
Panthers.

Julius Page made 10-of-15 shots en route to 21 points and Chevy
Troutman added 18 as Pittsburgh continued to dominate at home
and against the Red Flash with an easy 90-69 triumph.

Shooting 63 percent from the field, Pittsburgh (2-0) was able to
post its 23rd straight win at home - the fourth-longest streak
in the nation.  The Panthers also improved to 27-0 all-time
against St. Francis.

Pittsburgh, which jumped out to a 28-19 lead midway through the
first half, also is 58-0 against Northeast Conference opponents.

Darshan Luckey had 23 points for the Red Flash, who shot just 35
percent (13-of-37) in the second half after making 15-of-28
attempts in the opening 20 minutes.

St. Francis (0-1) was 14-14 last season and opens this campaign
with four straight road contests.
